Finally, it can be shown that probabilities can be replaced by truth values without any information being lost i.e, we can effectively replace the probability measure with the collection of truth values $\mathrm{\Gamma }{\underline{\mathrm{\Omega }}}^{Sh\left({\left(0,1\right)}_L\right)}$ for classical probability and $\mathrm{\Gamma }({\underline{\mathrm{\Omega }}}^{sh{(\mathcal{V}(\mathcal{K})\times (0,1)}_L)})$ for quantum probability [45]. It means that there is the following commutative diagram for classical probability
